            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>244 West 42 N.Yk.<lb/>
                Aug 20&#47;78<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais										
            Rev. and dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I see with extreme<lb/> pleasure that you also are advocating<lb/> the cause of the sufferers in Morocco.<lb/>  As you are doubtless aware the Bd. of<lb/> Delegates is about to take action upon<lb/> the matter&#44; but its efforts are directed<lb/> for the benefit of the Jews only&#44; which the<lb/> appeal made by the minister whose<lb/> names you have doubtless seen&#44; are an<lb/>nounced to be for the benefit of all<lb/> sufferers without distinction of race<lb/> or creed.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I forwarded a draft to Sir Moses<lb/> Montefiore last week&#44; altogether<lb/> &#36;290 (two hundred and ninety dollars&#41;<lb/> have been sent&#44; and I have<lb/> some &#36;130 still to send exclusive<lb/> of Dr Jottheil&#91;&#63;&#93; Heutrel&#91;&#63;&#93; Etc&#58;<lb/></p> 
            <p>With kind regards<lb/>
            I am dear sir<lb/>
            very truly<lb/>
            H &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
